============================================================
  PHILOSOPHY
============================================================

Concept:      Descartes' Cogito
Branch:       Epistemology
Definition:   I think therefore I am — the one undoubtable truth
Philosopher:  Rene Descartes
Example:      Even if deceived, you must exist to be deceived

Concept:      Stoicism
Branch:       Ethics
Definition:   Focus only on what is in your control; accept all else with equanimity
Philosopher:  Marcus Aurelius/Epictetus
Example:      Illness is not in your control; your response to it is

Concept:      Determinism
Branch:       Metaphysics
Definition:   All events are causally determined by prior events and natural laws
Philosopher:  Laplace/Spinoza
Example:      If universe were rewound exactly, every event would repeat identically

============================================================
  QUESTION & ANSWER PAIRS
============================================================

Q1: What is an algorithm?
A1: An algorithm is a step-by-step procedure for solving a
     problem. Algorithms have inputs, defined steps, and
     outputs. Examples: sorting, searching, path-finding.

Q2: What is natural selection?
A2: Natural selection: individuals with traits better
     suited to their environment survive and reproduce more.
     Over many generations, these traits become more common
     in the population.

Q3: What is the Big Bang?
A3: The Big Bang theory states the universe began from an
     extremely hot, dense point approximately 13.8 billion
     years ago and has been expanding ever since.

Q4: What is artificial intelligence?
A4: AI is the simulation of human intelligence by machines,
     including learning, reasoning, and problem-solving.
     Types: narrow AI (specific tasks) and general AI
     (human-level across domains).

Q5: What is the greenhouse effect?
A5: Greenhouse gases (CO2, methane) trap heat radiated from
     Earth's surface. Natural effect warms Earth; human
     emissions intensify it causing climate change.

